      "question": "During an investigation of ABC Manufacturing's financial statements, you discover that management has capitalized $2.5 million in routine repair and maintenance expenses as fixed assets. Additionally, inventory obsolescence reserves have been understated by $800,000, and the company has failed to record $1.2 million in accrued warranty liabilities. Which of the following BEST describes the combined effect of these manipulations on ABC Manufacturing's financial statements?",
